==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sola
<hw>So"la</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A leguminous plant (<spn>Aeschynomene
aspera</spn>) growing in moist places in Southern India and the East
Indies. Its pithlike stem is used for making hats, swimming-jackets,
etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>solah</asp>,
<asp>shola</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solace</ent>⟦br⟧

